Package com.google.code.jyield

Interface Summary
Generator<T> A generator is some object that is able to construct one or more objects and to submit them to the yieldable object.
GeneratorToIterableConverter<T> A class that can convert a generator to an iterable object.
IterableToGeneratorConverter<T> Converts an Iterable object to a generator.
Yieldable<T> An object to which it is possible to yield a result.
 

Class Summary
Loggable Provides classes with added logging capabilities and simplifies logging.
Main This is the project's main class, providing the main program entry point as well as the ability to parse the program's commandline arguments.
TrivialInterfaceConverter<T> A trivial implementation of a GeneratorToIterableConverter.
YieldUtils A utilities class for dealing with generators and iterators.
